<div class="span1">
  <br/><%= link_to 'Edit HR profile', edit_hr_profile_position_path %>
  <%= link_to 'Home', home_index_path, :class => 'btn' %>
</div>

<div class="span8">

  <h2>Human Resources Profile</h2>
  <hr />

  <table class="table">
    <tr>
      <th>Personal details</th>
      <th></th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Name</td>
      <td><%= @position.name %></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Date of Birth</td>
      <td><%= @position.birth_date.strftime("%d %B %Y") unless @position.birth_date.nil? %></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Age</td>
      <td><%= @position.age %></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Gender</td>
      <td><%= @position.gender %></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Nationality</td>
      <td><%= @position.nationality %></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Residential Status</td>
      <td><%= @position.res_status %></td>
    </tr>
  </table>

  <table class="table">
    <tr>
      <th>Job related details</th>
      <th></th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Start date of employement</td>
      <td><%= @position.start_date.strftime("%d %B %Y") unless @position.start_date.nil? %></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Type of contract</td>
      <td><%= @position.type_contract %></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Next Performance Appraisal</td>
      <td><%= @position.next_performance_talk.strftime("%d %B %Y") unless @position.next_performance_talk.nil? %></td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  <hr />

</div>

<div class="span3">
  <br/>
  <h4>About</h4>
  <p>This part is very important since it can contain some valueable data like salary, overal competency level and basic data like age and gender. If this specific info gets into the database it would be easy to build report tools which presents a nice overview of the current state inside an NRO (like diversity). This simplifies the reporting process and working in excel. This data could be rendered into excel and pdf formats (or even word).</p>
  <h4>Legal aspect</h4>
  <p>The info which goes to the livescreen is just standard info. So name will not be processed. However it is a neat function to have on a operational level because it gives the HR manager the opportunity to search by name as well as by position. The reports generated by the livescreen will not contain any names, merely standard data and charts. Just like the salary analysis which will just contain the position (job title), no personal names.</p>
</div>
